Dr. Muck carried out his ideas as to unity of style in the programme of the third evening concert of the Boston Symphony Orchestra given last evening in Carnegie Hall. It was made up entirely of modern works, except for two of the airs sung by Miss Elena Gerhardt, who was the soloist. View Full Article in Timesmachine Â»
